terms.medium_def:
Jeremiah's servant living at the time of Divided Monarchy, first mentioned at Jer.32.12; 
only referred to as Baruch (בָּרוּךְ); 
son of Neriah; 
a brother of Seraiah.

Asaph's father from the tribe of Levi living at the time of Divided Monarchy, first mentioned at 1Ch.6.39; 
only referred to as Berechiah (בֶּרֶכְיָה); 
a son of Shimea; 
father of Asaph.

A man living at the time of Exile and Return, first mentioned at Neh.3.4; 
only referred to as Berechiah (בֶּרֶכְיָה); 
a son of Meshezabel; 
father of Meshullam.

A man living at the time of the Patriarchs, first mentioned at Job.32.2; 
only referred to as Barachel (בָּרַכְאֵל); 
father of Elihu. § father of Elihu

A man living at the time of Exile and Return, first mentioned at Zec.1.1; 
only referred to as Berechiah (בֶּרֶכְיָה); 
a son of Iddo; 
father of Zechariah.

A man living at the time of Exile and Return, only mentioned at Neh.3.20; 
only referred to as Baruch (בָּרוּךְ); 
a son of Zabbai.

A man living at the time of Exile and Return, only mentioned at Neh.11.5; 
only referred to as Baruch (בָּרוּךְ); 
a son of Col-hozeh ; 
father of Maaseiah.

A man from the tribe of Judah living at the time of Divided Monarchy, only mentioned at 1Ch.3.20; 
only referred to as Berechiah (בֶּרֶכְיָה); 
son of Zerubbabel; 
a brother of Meshullam, Hananiah, Shelomith, Hashubah, Ohel, Hasadiah, Jushab-hesed, Abiud.

A man from the tribe of Levi living at the time of Exile and Return, only mentioned at 1Ch.9.16; 
only referred to as Berechiah (בֶּרֶכְיָה); 
a son of Asa.

A man living at the time of Divided Monarchy, only mentioned at 2Ch.28.12; 
only referred to as Berechiah (בֶּרֶכְיָה); 
a son of Meshillemoth.

A man living at the time of Divided Monarchy, only mentioned at Isa.8.2; 
only referred to as Jeberechiah (יְבֶרֶכְיָ֫הוּ); 
father of Zechariah. § father of a Zechariah, in the reign of Ahaz and time of Isaiah
